parfit - releases
=================

A release is a single commit on dev.  release-plz watches the
trunk, and whenever there are unreleased conventional commits, it
opens a "Release vX.Y.Z" PR whose contents are a Cargo.toml
version bump and the CHANGELOG entries for every commit since the
last tag.  Merging that PR is the release: the commit lands on
dev, publish.yml publishes the crate and tags the commit, and
goreleaser fires on the tag to upload prebuilt binaries and push
the Homebrew formula.

rel tracks the last release.  The release workflow fast-forwards
the rel branch to the tagged commit, so rel is a pointer to the
current published version and never leads dev.

Conventional commits matter for the release bot.  release-plz
reads every commit subject to decide the semver bump (feat →
minor, fix → patch, trailing `!` or `BREAKING CHANGE:` → major)
and to write the CHANGELOG section for each one.  A commit like

    feat(source): recognize and reflow block comments

lands under `### Added` in the CHANGELOG with the subject as the
entry text.  A commit like

    fix(walker): use io::Error::other per clippy's io_other_error lint

lands under `### Fixed`.  Non-conventional subjects don't parse
and end up in `### Other` or get skipped entirely, so the
commitlint PR gate rejects them at review time.  The log stays
clean and the changelog auto-generates without manual curation.
